<div class="content">
  <h2>Beginner vs Enthusiast Guide</h2>
  <p>Choosing the right espresso machine depends heavily on your willingness to learn the craft versus your desire for a quick, hassle-free morning coffee.</p>

  <div class="guide-grid">
    <div class="guide-box">
      <h3>For Beginners & Convenience Seekers</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Super-Automatics:</strong> Machines like the <strong>De'Longhi Magnifica</strong> or <strong>Jura E8</strong> handle everything from grinding to extracting. Perfect if you just want to push a button.</li>
        <li><strong>Pod Machines:</strong> The <strong>Nespresso Vertuo</strong> offers ultimate ease of use, though you sacrifice the flavor of freshly ground beans.</li>
        <li><strong>Entry Semi-Autos:</strong> The <strong>Breville Bambino</strong> is forgiving and heats up almost instantly, making it a great stepping stone.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="guide-box">
      <h3>For Enthusiasts & Hobbyists</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Prosumer Semi-Autos:</strong> The <strong>Gaggia Classic Pro</strong> and <strong>Rancilio Silvia</strong> feature commercial components like 58mm portafilters. They require skill to dial in but produce cafe-quality shots.</li>
        <li><strong>All-in-Ones:</strong> The <strong>Breville Barista Express</strong> strikes a balance, offering an enthusiast experience with the convenience of an integrated grinder.</li>
        <li><strong>Essential Add-on:</strong> True enthusiasts must budget for a high-quality separate burr grinder.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
  <div class="faq-list">
    <div class="faq-item">
      <div class="faq-q">What is the difference between a semi-automatic and super-automatic espresso machine?</div>
      <div class="faq-a">A semi-automatic machine requires you to manually grind, tamp the coffee, and start/stop the water flow. A super-automatic machine does all of this at the push of a button, grinding, brewing, and even frothing milk automatically.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="faq-item">
      <div class="faq-q">Do I need a built-in grinder for an espresso machine?</div>
      <div class="faq-a">Not necessarily. While a built-in grinder saves counter space and offers convenience, many enthusiasts prefer a separate, dedicated espresso grinder as it allows for finer, more consistent adjustments.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="faq-item">
      <div class="faq-q">What is the best espresso machine for beginners?</div>
      <div class="faq-a">For true beginners, pod machines like the Nespresso Vertuo are the easiest. For those wanting to learn authentic espresso-making, the Breville Bambino or Barista Express are highly recommended due to their fast heat-up times and user-friendly features.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="faq-item">
      <div class="faq-q">How often should I descale my espresso machine?</div>
      <div class="faq-a">It depends on your water hardness and usage, but generally, you should descale every 2 to 3 months. If your machine has a built-in water filter, make sure to replace it according to the manufacturer's instructions.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="faq-item">
      <div class="faq-q">Are pod espresso machines as good as traditional ones?</div>
      <div class="faq-a">Pod machines offer unbeatable convenience and consistency but generally cannot match the rich, full-bodied flavor, authentic crema, and customization of a traditional semi-automatic machine using freshly ground beans.</div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<script is:inline>
  const headers = document.querySelectorAll('th[data-sort]');
  const rows = document.querySelectorAll('.brand-row');
  const tableBody = document.getElementById('tableBody');

  // Sort logic
  headers.forEach(header => {
    header.addEventListener('click', () => {
      const sortType = header.getAttribute('data-sort');
      const isAsc = !header.classList.contains('asc');

      headers.forEach(h => { h.classList.remove('asc', 'desc'); });
      header.classList.add(isAsc ? 'asc' : 'desc');

      const rowsArray = Array.from(rows);

      rowsArray.sort((a, b) => {
        let aVal, bVal;

        if (sortType === 'brand') {
          aVal = a.children[0].innerText.toLowerCase();
          bVal = b.children[0].innerText.toLowerCase();
        } else if (sortType === 'type') {
          aVal = a.children[1].innerText.toLowerCase();
          bVal = b.children[1].innerText.toLowerCase();
        } else if (sortType === 'price') {
          aVal = a.children[2].innerText.length; // Compare number of '$'
          bVal = b.children[2].innerText.length;
        } else if (sortType === 'grinder') {
          aVal = a.children[3].innerText.includes('✓') ? 1 : 0;
          bVal = b.children[3].innerText.includes('✓') ? 1 : 0;
        } else if (sortType === 'steam') {
          aVal = a.children[4].innerText.includes('✓') ? 1 : 0;
          bVal = b.children[4].innerText.includes('✓') ? 1 : 0;
        } else if (sortType === 'water') {
          aVal = parseInt(a.children[5].innerText) || 0;
          bVal = parseInt(b.children[5].innerText) || 0;
        } else if (sortType === 'ease') {
          const easeOrder = { 'low': 1, 'moderate': 2, 'high': 3, 'very high': 4 };
          aVal = easeOrder[a.children[6].innerText.toLowerCase()] || 0;
          bVal = easeOrder[b.children[6].innerText.toLowerCase()] || 0;
        }

        if (aVal < bVal) return isAsc ? -1 : 1;
        if (aVal > bVal) return isAsc ? 1 : -1;
        return 0;
      });

      rowsArray.forEach(row => tableBody.appendChild(row));
    });
  });
</script>

